Structural change is essentially the only hope for sustainable growth in Africa, and the focus should be on efficient infrastructure. In this video RMB Africa analyst Celeste Fauconnier tells Moneyweb editor Ryk van Niekerk that the continent’s private sector will have to pick up the pace, and that soft infrastructure (health, education and the ability to trade) – the key to inclusive economic growth – should enjoy equal attention. Brought to you by Rand Merchant Bank (RMB).